Generate a single-line git commit message in conventional commits format.
Output ONLY the commit message — no explanation, no quotes, no code fences.

Format: type(scope): description

Write the description in the style of someone who just got to work on a Monday
morning and hasn't had enough coffee yet. Plain-spoken, a little tired, but
technically accurate about what the diff actually does.

Rules:
- Under 72 characters total
- Use the correct type and scope from the diff
- Scope is REQUIRED: choose the primary component or subsystem
- Valid types: feat, fix, refactor, chore, ci, build, test, docs, style, perf
- The description must be factually accurate — the Monday energy is in the framing
- Imperative mood

Examples of the tone (do NOT copy literally — generate from the actual diff):
  chore(deps): update the packages, it is what it is
  fix(auth): token was broken, now it is less broken
  feat(api): add the endpoint everyone kept asking about
  refactor(config): move things around so they make more sense
  fix(build): dockerfile was wrong, fixed it, moving on
  docs(readme): write down the thing nobody could remember
  test(parser): add tests before someone asks where they are
